<h2>Audit</h2>
<p>The reference runtime for the <a href="/projects/webaudit/">Web Audit</a> protocol — a domain entity's
immutable, actor-attributed history. The block ships the protocol's seam and nothing about the store
behind it.</p>

<h3>What it provides</h3>
<ul>
  <li><code>AuditEvent</code> — the normalized record
    (<code>{ target, action, actor, at, before?, after?, correlationId? }</code>); <code>before</code>/
    <code>after</code> reuse the <a href="/projects/webstates/">Web States</a> <code>ChangeRecord</code>
    shape.</li>
  <li><code>CustomAuditProvider</code> — the swappable contract: <code>append()</code> (immutable),
    <code>queryByEntity()</code>, optional <code>subscribe()</code>.</li>
  <li><code>DefaultAuditProvider</code> — a native-first, in-memory, <strong>append-only</strong> reference
    that freezes each event (never mutates or deletes — the property regulated audit depends on).</li>
  <li><code>CustomAuditRegistry</code> (<code>window.customAudit</code>) — named providers the project
    selects or overrides via the injector chain.</li>
  <li><code>auditLifecycle()</code> — the headline composition: subscribes a
    <a href="/projects/weblifecycle/">Web Lifecycle</a> provider so every transition becomes one
    <code>AuditEvent</code> automatically.</li>
</ul>

<h3>What it deliberately does not own</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>The before/after vocabulary</strong> — reused from Web States change-tracking, not
    redefined.</li>
  <li><strong>The timeline UI</strong> — the canonical per-entity render is the
    <a href="/intents/audit-timeline/">Audit Timeline</a> intent (the <code>audit-timeline</code> block).</li>
  <li><strong>Durability / retention / tamper-evidence</strong> — provider concerns; the default is an
    in-memory log, a real deployment plugs in an event-sourced or OSCAL-aligned backend.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Composition</h3>
<p>The first real consumer is the
<a href="/backlog/317-exercise-app-loan-origination/">loan-origination exercise app</a>, where the
lifecycle provider's transitions auto-feed the audit log and the timeline renders the selected loan's
history. <a href="/backlog/351-web-compliance-project/">Web Compliance</a> can reuse the
<code>AuditEvent</code> schema at the platform level.</p>
